#: ../../../src/dev/metal_logging.rst:2
msgid "Metal Logging"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../src/dev/metal_logging.rst:4
msgid ""
"In debug builds, MLX compiles Metal kernels with ``os_log`` enabled so "
"shader warnings and debug messages are visible during development."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../src/dev/metal_logging.rst:8
msgid ""
"Metal logging is only available with Metal 3.2 or higher (macOS 15 and up, "
"iOS 18 and up)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../src/dev/metal_logging.rst:11
msgid "To enable logging from kernels, first make sure to build in debug mode:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../src/dev/metal_logging.rst:13
msgid "DEBUG=1 python -m pip install -e ."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../src/dev/metal_logging.rst:17
msgid ""
"Then, in the kernel source code include MLX's logging shim and use ``mlx::"
"os_log``:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../src/dev/metal_logging.rst:20
msgid ""
"#include \"mlx/backend/metal/kernels/logging.h\"\n"
"\n"
"constant mlx::os_log logger(\"mlx\", \"my_kernel\");\n"
"\n"
"kernel void my_kernel(/* ... */) {\n"
"// ...\n"
"  logger.log_debug(\"unexpected state: idx=%u\", idx);\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../src/dev/metal_logging.rst:31
msgid ""
"When you run the program, set the Metal log level to your desired level and "
"forward logs to ``stderr``:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../src/dev/metal_logging.rst:34
msgid "MTL_LOG_LEVEL=MTLLogLevelDebug MTL_LOG_TO_STDERR=1 python script.py"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../src/dev/metal_logging.rst:38
msgid "See the `Metal logging guide`_ for more details."
msgstr ""
